<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-16T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-16T20:00:00-05:00" n="731" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d731">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.1561/26: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Walton</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-16T21:00:00-04:00">December
                                    16, 1943—9 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>139. The Department does not understand, reference your telegram no. 211,
                            December 13, what is meant by “a municipal corporation with obligation
                            appertaining to such corporation”. Please elaborate, particularly as
                            regards how Americans could participate in a Liberian municipal
                            corporation.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>